**Evidence-based methods for learning and self-development:**  
\- learning pyramid (teaching and practice instead of passive reading/watching)  
\- time-boxing/time-blocking  
\- habit stacking  
\- implementation intentions  
\- Eisenhower matrix  
\- Pomodoro  
\- spaced repetitions  
\- daily rhythm (maintaining some sort of exercise routine and order)  
\- create momentum  
\- TODO lists for work and complex things  
\- removing distractions  
\- changing workplace during the day  
\- early/late windows  
\- days for specific areas  
\- switching between focused and diffusive thinking modes for problem-solving (zooming in / zooming out)  
\- write everything down and keep it organized in one place \- tasks, action items, project points of contact, etc.  
\- be prepared for the questions to overcome the problems with fast answers 

How to achieve long-term goals, short-term goals, and follow continious or repeatable tasks consistently? Write down the list of objectives, make a schedule, use technics (pareto rule 80/20, Esinghower matrix, pomodoro technic, time-boxing and time-blocking, etc.)
